The PM announced plans today to raise the price of a pack of cigarettes to the equivalent of R150. JOHANNESBURG - The cost of lighting up at a French sidewalk cafe may finally dissuade even the most ardent smoker if Prime Minister (PM) Edouard Phillippe gets his way.The PM announced plans today to raise the price of a pack of cigarettes to the equivalent of R150.He says with 80 000 tobacco-related deaths in France each year, doing nothing is simply not an option.